# JavaScript SOP

- Use strict mode in modules; prefer ESM (`import`/`export`) when project allows.
- JSDoc types on public APIs when TS migration is not in scope.
- Prefer `const`/`let`; no implicit globals; handle promise rejections.
- No secrets in source; validate env at startup.
- Match eslint/prettier; run lint before commit.
- Tests: colocate `*.test.js` or `__tests__/` per project convention.
- Node scripts: shebang only when executable; use `cli-python.mdc` for argparse-heavy CLIs in `.py` — for Node use consistent commander/yargs per repo.
